Package bturnert_a1.ePortfolio

Class MutualFund

java.lang.Object
bturnert_a1.ePortfolio.MutualFund
public class MutualFund extends Object
This class creates and edits objects of type MutualFund.

MutualFund contains inforamtion on a MutualFund's name, symbol, price, quantity, and book value

    • buyUpdateBookValue

      public void buyUpdateBookValue​(double tempPrice, int tempQuantity)
      Updates the current MutualFund's book value to the result of adding the multiplication of the updated MutualFund's price by the new quantity and adding the commission fee to the current book value.
      Parameters:
      tempPrice - Double passed to method representing the new Price for the MutualFund object.
      tempQuantity - Integer passed to method representing the new quantity of the MutualFund being bought.

    • sellUpdateQuantity

      public int sellUpdateQuantity()
      Prompts the user for the quantity of the current MutualFund object to be sold. Scans an integer from system.in and removes what was read from the current MutualFund's quantity. Prints the gain from selling the specified quantity of the MutualFund object If after selling, the quantity for the current MutualFund object equals 0, returns 1. If after selling, the quantity for the current MutualFund object does not equal 0, updates the book value for the current MutualFund object and returns 0.

      Loops until a valid integer value is entered by the user.

      Returns:
      Returns either the interger 0 representing that not all of the MutualFund object was sold or 1 representing all of the MutualFund object was sold.

    • getGain

      public double getGain()
      Calculates the gain aquired if all currently held MutualFund objects were sold completely at their current prices.
      Returns:
      Returns a double representing the gain aquired if all currently held MutualFund objects were sold completely at their current prices.
